result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew J Parisi was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(1).
  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.
  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.
  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.
  • Deliver Illegal Articles to Inmate [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 302.095(2).
  • Deliver Illegal Articles to Inmate [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 302.095(2).
  • Deliver Illegal Articles to Inmate [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 302.095(2).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
